Reasoning: The paper deals with the asymptotic behavior of mutual information, symbol-error probability, and minimum mean-square error for a communication channel, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The study of bit-interleaved coded modulation (BICM) also suggests a possible fit for the Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI) and Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of constellation points and Gray codes points towards a possible fit for the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
